  "lyric": "杨乃文 - Diamonds Are Forever<br>\n专辑：《Self-Selected》<br>\n<br>\nDiamonds are forever<br>\nThey are all I need to please me<br>\nThey can stimulate and tease me<br>\nThey won't leave in the night<br>\nI've no fear that they might desert me<br>\n<br>\nDiamonds are forever<br>\nHold one up and then caress it<br>\nTouch it, stroke it and undress it<br>\nI can see every part<br>\nNothing hides in the heart to hurt me<br>\nI don't need love<br>\nFor what good will love do me<br>\nDiamonds never lie to me<br>\nFor when love's gone<br>\nThey'll luster on<br>\nDiamonds are forever<br>\nSparkling round my little finger<br>\nUnlike men, the diamonds linger<br>\nMen are mere mortals who<br>\nAre not worth going to your grave for<br>\n<br>\nI don't need love<br>\nFor what good will love do me<br>\nDiamonds never lie to me<br>\nFor when love's gone<br>\nThey'll luster on<br>\nDiamonds are forever, forever, forever<br>\nDiamonds are forever, forever, forever<br>\nForever and ever",
